node.text:
Would you dare to walk on this Via Ferrata? 😳 Share your posts with us and we will share them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

The new Signora Delle Acque, in the Ruzza river, is a highly emotional and spectacular via ferrata that gives you unforgettable emotions; the sight embraces whole Trentino, but keeping fixed on the track too.

📽 @niklaskoessel
📍Trentino, Italy

node.text:
CrusHIIT Full Body 🤩 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process.

Tell me about your favorite vacation spot 🏝

SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT 👊🏼

I personally would love a few days off 😅. It’s been so busy with upcoming projects, so right about now, swimming in the ocean and chilling under an umbrella with a cold drink, somewhere tropical, sounds dreamy. Soon, soon hopefully 🙏🏻

Workout deets: 45 secs ON 15 secs OFF (beginners modify as necessary and start with 15-30 secs then rest for 45-30 secs): 3-4 rounds

📽 @senada.greca

TRAIN SMARTER NOT HARDER! 💪 We can promote your photos in our account. Click the link in our bio for instructions: @RunningTerritory 

Keep over 90 % of your training under your IMAT HR for at least 6 months to see dramatic improvements

Since January, I have made sure well over 90% of my training was kept under my INDIVIDUAL MAXIMUM AEROBIC TRAINING ( IMAT) heart rate.

How to calculate your IMAT :
It is very simple if you know your maximum heart rate it is
MAX HR - 40

If you do not know it, MAF formula is a good starting point
180-AGE = Max Aerobic Function

Both formulae attempt to predict your max aerobic HR without an expensive lab test

In 8 months I have managed to extend my aerobic fitness from 5km at 4:30/ at around 115HR to today when I ran 40km at 4:30 pace with 116 Ave HR

HOW ?
Running at no higher than my Max aerobic HR -40( IMAT)
My max HR is 170 - 40 = 130 as my max aerobic HR.

BENEFIT:
One big benefit of staying aerobic for me, preparing for an Ironman Triathlon, is it has allowed me to do much bigger volumes of training without getting sick or injured. Something anaerobic training does not allow.

Train Smarter Not Harder
Don’t let anyone tell you getting older makes you slow, I am 60 next year, so we all have plenty of time to work on aerobic development. 😉

If you like what I write please share this and tag your friends. Got a comment 👇
